review:
Started the game at 5pm;
lost all sense of time;
left the computer at 5pm next day;
fingers hurt.
Eagerly still waiting;
for another session.

Lovely multiplayer continuation of Don't Starve, adding some stuff and story. 
Pro:
+ Pretty art style;
+ Lovely atmosphere;
+ Nice music and sound effects;
+ Fun cooperative survival experience;
+ Continuation of the story of Don't Starve (yes, there's a story); 
+ Up to 8 free skin items dropping randomly every week during gameplay and 1 daily drop on launch.
+ Paid DLCs can be accessed for free via spools.
Con:
- Some poor balance decisions from Klei compared to singleplayer game.

